Depending on accomplishments or other 
attention, Kirkland Kerr. Kerr, K-E-R-R. He went

06:50.433 --> 06:51.434
to LSU, didn't he? No, no. Well, he went to LSU, but 
then he went on. He's ill. All right,

06:54.768 --> 07:10.792
let's make believe that you...

06:54.768 --> 07:10.792
Who's that? Oh, Roger is one of your graduate

07:10.812 --> 07:19.546
students? Mm-hmm. Let's make believe that you've 
now just been hired as a consultant to give advice

07:20.215 --> 07:30.745
today to the Dean of Veterinary Medicine at Texas 
A&M. What advice would you give the Dean of

07:30.845 --> 07:34.068
Veterinary Medicine today?

07:39.593 --> 07:50.003
The Dean of Veterinary Medicine has to work on, 
it's fairly cool, for the faculty, individual

07:39.593 --> 07:50.003
faculty member, that he knows that that faculty 
member needs to excel for his own good and

07:50.810 --> 07:59.142
academically, which means being a scholar and 
being a good teacher. And then he should organize

08:00.404 --> 08:04.210
so he can promote that. And I think that

08:05.992 --> 08:19.652
I've got a lot of thanks for that.

08:29.453 --> 08:30.595
What are you going to tell him then? We just funded a 
chair in medical education.

08:40.168 --> 08:44.314
What they proposed may not be what I want to see. I 
would like to see a situation where a teacher can

08:44.334 --> 08:57.773
teach and a student comes to him wanting 
knowledge, but he does not have to quiz that

08:44.334 --> 08:57.773
student. by challenging them, but they can work 
together to accomplish this. Now, I know that's

09:04.920 --> 09:12.291
contrary to the great authoritarian power of the 
faculty member. But to me, it would be just a

09:13.553 --> 09:21.466
wonderful experience to be in a situation where a 
student comes to you, and he wants you. I don't

09:21.546 --> 09:22.628
understand this. And you feel like you can talk to 
him. Whether we're not worried about giving them

09:25.951 --> 09:30.275
the answer to the question you're going to ask. 
Sounds like a good plan to me. Yeah. I would love to

09:32.297 --> 09:33.518
see that. And that's what they're fortunate with 
this, is it'll work with young faculty.

09:47.631 --> 09:49.392
That was the advice for the department. No, that 
was for the dean. For the dean. OK. Now, what advice

09:52.355 --> 09:55.958
would you give to the department?

09:58.435 --> 09:59.376
Or an apartment head? Either way. Well, I think 
that each faculty member needs an apartment head

10:01.019 --> 10:09.391
that nobody respects.

10:11.574 --> 10:18.423
And I always had this philosophy, and I think I got 
this, I guess, from the years of Earl Broder.

10:23.651 --> 10:25.253
His philosophy was... I propose a raise for this 
person or a promotion and his answer would be, you

10:27.190 --> 10:42.312
hired this person and he told me he was a good 
teacher, he's going to be an excellent person.

10:42.332 --> 10:52.107
He's a leader in his field and we paid, set a budget 
to pay him for this and we're paying him for that.

10:53.168 --> 10:54.210
What has he done now? to warrant this. Tell me. 
Don't tell me again he's a good teacher. And I feel

11:03.459 --> 11:15.018
like that if department heads could approach the 
thing, what can I do for you today? And if I go as your

11:15.118 --> 11:24.012
representative to the dean, what can I tell the 
dean that you're done? Now, were you a believer in

11:26.000 --> 11:29.484
merit salary? Oh, yes. And I believe in demerit 
salaries. Because I think that there is such a

11:35.111 --> 11:53.374
thing that faculty members take, some faculty 
members take a job,

11:35.111 --> 11:53.374
this is mine, I'm going to do this, and they'll say, 
this is an opportunity for me. And those that want a

11:53.394 --> 11:55.517
position And there's one thing, a difference from 
those who want opportunity. And I think that needs

12:01.620 --> 12:08.811
to be conveyed to the faculty by the department 
heads in such a way. And I think one of the problems

12:08.831 --> 12:18.687
is that people are hired now not knowing that they 
may want to expect it at a certain time because

12:08.831 --> 12:18.687
nobody says so.

